ProcedureHelp.#cdata:
Syntax: PROC RANK <option(s)>;  
      BY <DESCENDING> variable-1 <...<DESCENDING> variable-n> <NOTSORTED>;  
      VAR data-set-variables(s);  
      RANKS new-variables(s);

The RANK procedure computes ranks for one or more numeric variables across the observations 
of a SAS data set and outputs the ranks to a new SAS data set. PROC RANK by itself produces 
no printed output.
